  "prompt": "What are the Japanese names that mean \"dragon\"?",
  "response": "In Japanese, there are several names that mean \"dragon.\" Some of these names include:\n\n1. **Ry\u016b (\u7adc or \u9f8d)** - This is the most straightforward name meaning \"dragon.\"\n2. **Tatsu (\u8fb0 or \u9f8d)** - Another common name that means \"dragon,\" often used in names or as a character in stories.\n3. **Seiryu (\u9752\u7adc)** - Meaning \"Azure Dragon,\" one of the four guardian spirits in Chinese mythology, which is also used in Japanese.\n4. **K\u014dry\u016b (\u9ec4\u7adc)** - Meaning \"Yellow Dragon.\"\n5. **Shory\u016b (\u6607\u7adc)** - Meaning \"Rising Dragon.\"\n\nThese names are often used in various contexts, including personal names, mythical creatures, and in cultural references.",
